The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 Dublin/Brussels, Nov. 17: Ireland has committed itself to working with an European Union-IMF mission on steps to help its stricken banking sector, a process that could lead to a bailout. A team from the European Commission, the International Monetary Fund and European Central Bank will travel to Ireland on Thursday to examine what measures may be needed if Dublin decides to seek aid, euro zone finance ministers said.                            
	 New Delhi, Nov. 17: A government report on steps to cut transaction costs for exporters will be implemented as soon as it is released, minister of state for commerce Jyotiraditya Scindia has said. The minister said a task force headed by him had been considering ways to bring down the transaction cost, which accounts for $13 billion, for exporters.                            
	 Mumbai, Nov. 17: The follow-on public offer (FPO) of the Shipping Corporation of India (SCI) is likely to hit the market by early-December, a senior official said. Meanwhile, Indian Oil Corporation has hired six investment banks, including Merrill Lynch, Citigroup and ICICI Securities, to handle its FPO.                            
	 New Delhi, Nov. 17: Mahindra Reva Electric Vehicles is working on introducing electricity-driven technology in Mahindra amp; Mahindras entire product portfolio, and a final announcement will be made in the next fiscal.                             
	 Geneva, Nov. 17: Switzerlands pharmaceutical giant Roche will slash 4,800 jobs worldwide in response to tough market conditions. The restructuring efforts are expected to result in savings of over 2 billion Swiss francs.                            
	 Hyderabad, Nov. 17: Honda Motorcycle and Scooter India will soon set up its third two-wheeler manufacturing facility near here with an investment of Rs 1,000 crore, a government official said.                            
	 Mumbai, Nov. 17: Indias gold imports are likely to cross the 750-tonne mark this year because of increasing consumer demand for jewellery despite soaring prices, the World Gold Council has said.
                                                                                                                          
